15/08/2003
BUCHAREST, Romania -- The Democratic Party and the National Liberal Party agreed on Thursday (14 August) to form an alliance. They also decided to appoint two negotiation teams to draw up a ruling programme, a decision-making system and a system to resolve conflicts within the future alliance. Each party plans to come up with its own candidate in the 2004 presidential elections. According to the latest opinion poll, published Thursday, an alliance between the liberals and the democrats would win 27 per cent of the votes in parliamentary elections. (Mediafax, Nine o'Clock - 14/08/03)
